# SPEC — WhatsApp Booking Agent (Phase 1)

**Project:** Revive Bookings — an AI agent on WhatsApp that books clients into classes at **Revive** (studio) via Wix Bookings, taking payment first via Wave (Senegal mobile money).

**Phone numbers:** Phase 1 runs entirely on **Meta's free test number** (WhatsApp Cloud API sandbox — messages limited to up to 5 pre-verified recipient numbers). A dedicated production number will be registered later; only `WA_PHONE_NUMBER_ID` and token change at that point — build nothing that assumes the test number. The studio's existing reception WhatsApp number stays outside this system and is used only as the human-handoff destination (`RECEPTION_PHONE`).

**Payment-first invariant:** a booking is NEVER created in Wix until a Wave payment webhook is verified. No exceptions.

---

## 1. Architecture

```
Client (WhatsApp)
   │  inbound msg
   ▼
Meta WhatsApp Cloud API ──webhook──► Backend ◄──webhook── Wave (payment events)
                                       │
                        ┌──────────────┼──────────────┐
                        ▼              ▼              ▼
                  Claude API      Wix Bookings     Postgres
                 (conversation)  (availability,   (state, logs)
                                  create booking)
```

Single deployable service. No frontend. All client interaction happens in WhatsApp.

## 2. Stack (opinionated — deviate only with good reason)

- **Node 20+ / TypeScript**, Fastify (or Express)
- **Postgres** (any managed instance; Railway/Render bundled is fine)
- **@anthropic-ai/sdk** for the agent loop, model `claude-sonnet-latest` (alias ok)
- Deployment target: Railway/Render/Fly.io. Must expose HTTPS for webhooks.
- Local dev: use a tunnel (ngrok/cloudflared) for webhook testing.

