## 4. External APIs

Consult official docs for exact request/response shapes — do not guess fields.

### 4.1 WhatsApp Cloud API
- Inbound: `POST {BASE_URL}/webhooks/whatsapp`. Also implement the `GET` challenge handshake (`hub.verify_token` / `hub.challenge`).
- Verify `X-Hub-Signature-256` (HMAC-SHA256 of raw body with `WA_APP_SECRET`) on every POST. Reject on mismatch.
- Outbound: `POST https://graph.facebook.com/v21.0/{WA_PHONE_NUMBER_ID}/messages` — text messages only for Phase 1 (no templates needed inside the 24h service window).
- Dedupe inbound by WhatsApp `message.id` (store processed IDs; webhooks retry).

### 4.2 Wix Bookings (REST, https://www.wixapis.com)
- Headers on every call: `Authorization: {WIX_API_KEY}`, `wix-site-id: {WIX_SITE_ID}`.
- **List services** (classes): Services API — used to populate the class catalog.
- **Query Availability**: Availability Calendar / Time Slots API — returns bookable slots; for class services each slot carries an `eventId`.
- **Create Booking** (Bookings V2): for classes, pass `bookedEntity.slot.eventId` exactly as returned by Query Availability, plus contact details (name, phone). Set the booking as paid-offline/already-paid so Wix does not expect payment.
- Docs root: https://dev.wix.com/docs/rest/business-solutions/bookings — verify exact endpoint paths there at build time.

### 4.3 Wave Checkout API (https://docs.wave.com/checkout)
- Create session: `POST https://api.wave.com/v1/checkout/sessions` with `Authorization: Bearer {WAVE_API_KEY}`. Body includes `amount` (string), `currency: "XOF"`, `client_reference` (our `pending_booking.id`), `success_url`, `error_url`. Response includes `wave_launch_url` → send this URL to the client in WhatsApp.
- Webhook: `POST {BASE_URL}/webhooks/wave`. Verify HMAC signature with `WAVE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` per Wave docs. Handle `checkout.session.completed`; match on `client_reference`. Process idempotently (a session may be delivered more than once).
- `success_url`/`error_url` can point to a minimal static "return to WhatsApp" page served by this app.

## 5. Data model (Postgres)

```sql
clients(
  id uuid pk, wa_phone text unique, name text,
  language text,               -- 'fr' | 'en' | 'wo', last detected
  created_at, updated_at
)

pending_bookings(
  id uuid pk,                  -- used as Wave client_reference
  client_id fk, service_id text, service_name text,
  event_id text,               -- Wix class event id
  slot_start timestamptz, slot_end timestamptz,
  amount_xof integer,
  status text,                 -- see state machine
  wave_session_id text, payment_link text, link_expires_at timestamptz,
  wix_booking_id text,         -- set after booking created
  payer_phone text,            -- from Wave webhook, informational
  created_at, updated_at
)

processed_webhooks(id text pk, source text, received_at)  -- idempotency

conversations(
  id uuid pk, client_id fk, role text, content text,      -- message log
  wa_message_id text, created_at
)

handoffs(id uuid pk, client_id fk, reason text, transcript_excerpt text, created_at)
```

### State machine — `pending_bookings.status`

```
DRAFT ──payment link created──► AWAITING_PAYMENT
AWAITING_PAYMENT ──TTL passed──────────────► EXPIRED
AWAITING_PAYMENT ──valid Wave webhook──────► PAID
PAID ──slot still free, Wix booking OK─────► BOOKED
PAID ──slot gone or Wix error──────────────► REFUND_NEEDED
```

- `EXPIRED`: if the client pays after expiry and the webhook still arrives, treat as `PAID` and continue normally (money was taken; honor it if the slot exists, else `REFUND_NEEDED`).
- `REFUND_NEEDED`: no automated refund in Phase 1. Notify the client ("we'll refund you within 24h"), record it, and expose it in the daily log for manual processing in the Wave portal.

## 6. Agent design

### Loop
Inbound WhatsApp message → load last ~20 conversation turns + client record → call Claude with system prompt + tools → execute tool calls → send final text reply via WhatsApp. Persist all turns.

### System prompt requirements
- Identity: booking assistant for **Revive** — friendly, brief, WhatsApp-appropriate (short messages, no markdown headers).
- **Language:** detect and mirror the client's language among French, English, Wolof. Default to French when ambiguous.
- Never invent classes, prices, or slots — always use tools.
- Never promise a booking before payment confirmation.
- Payment flow to communicate: "I'll send you a Wave link; your spot is confirmed once paid. Link valid 20 minutes."
- Escalate to human (tool) for: complaints, refunds, rescheduling/cancelling existing bookings, medical questions, anything off-script. Handoff message includes `RECEPTION_PHONE`.

### Tools

| Tool | Args | Behavior |
|---|---|---|
| `list_classes` | none | Wix Services API → name, description, price, duration. Cache 10 min. |
| `check_availability` | `service_id`, `date_from`, `date_to` | Wix availability → slots with remaining spots + `event_id`. Never show full slots. |
| `create_payment_link` | `service_id`, `event_id`, `slot_start`, `client_name` | Creates `pending_booking` (DRAFT), re-verifies slot, creates Wave session, sets AWAITING_PAYMENT, returns link + expiry to include in the reply. |
| `get_my_bookings` | none | Client's bookings from our DB (BOOKED, upcoming). |
| `handoff_to_human` | `reason` | Records handoff, returns the reception number for the reply. |

Constraint: one active `AWAITING_PAYMENT` per client; creating a new link cancels (EXPIRED) the previous one.

## 7. Wave webhook handler (critical path)

1. Verify signature. 401 on failure. Log attempt.
2. Idempotency check via `processed_webhooks`.
3. Look up `pending_booking` by `client_reference`. Unknown ref → log warning, 200 (don't retry-loop).
4. Set `PAID`.
5. **Re-check slot in Wix.** If free → Create Booking → `BOOKED` → WhatsApp confirmation message (class, date/time, address, "show this message at reception"). If gone → `REFUND_NEEDED` → apologetic WhatsApp message offering alternative slots (agent picks up the conversation).
6. Always return 200 quickly; do Wix/WhatsApp work async if needed (queue or fire-and-forget with retry).

## 8. Edge cases (must handle)

- Duplicate webhook deliveries (both Meta and Wave) → idempotent.
- Client sends new messages while payment pending → agent answers normally, reminds about the link.
- Two clients racing for the last spot → whoever's webhook lands first wins; loser → REFUND_NEEDED flow.
- Voice notes/images/stickers inbound → polite text reply asking for text (Phase 1: no transcription).
- Unknown/garbled language → default French.
- Wix or Wave API down → agent apologizes, offers reception handoff; never fabricates.
- Message from a group chat or status → ignore.

## 9. Security

- Verify signatures on BOTH webhooks; reject unsigned/invalid.
- Secrets only via env vars; never logged.
- No payment card data anywhere (Wave handles all payment UI).
- Rate-limit inbound processing per phone (e.g. 20 msgs/min) to bound API spend.
- Prompt-injection stance: tools are the only side effects; tool inputs validated server-side (e.g. `event_id` must come from a prior availability result stored server-side, not trusted from model output alone — keep a per-conversation slot cache and validate against it).

## 10. Testing & acceptance

**Test setup:** Meta test number (5 verified recipients) + mocked Wave webhook endpoint (a script that POSTs signed payloads), OR real 100 XOF payments once Wave access granted.

Acceptance checklist — all must pass:

1. Happy path FR: greet → list classes → pick slot → pay (simulated webhook) → Wix booking exists → confirmation received on WhatsApp.
2. Same in EN and Wolof (language mirrored).
3. Expired link: no booking created; client can request a fresh link.
4. Forged Wave webhook (bad signature) → rejected, no state change.
5. Duplicate Wave webhook → exactly one Wix booking.
6. Slot-taken race → REFUND_NEEDED recorded, client notified, no Wix booking.
7. "I want to cancel my class" → handoff with reception number, handoff row recorded.
8. Restart the service mid-flow → no lost state (everything in Postgres).
9. Unit tests: both signature verifiers, state machine transitions.

## 11. Non-goals (Phase 1)

Orange Money; automated refunds; rescheduling/cancellation by the agent; WhatsApp templates/reminders; receptionist dashboard (a daily plain-text summary log or email is enough); voice note transcription; migrating the reception number.

